# Toronto Rental Market Analysis
## Overview

This project investigates how property characteristics and market exposure influence rental prices in Toronto. Using rental listing data, we developed and evaluated multiple linear regression models to identify factors associated with rental pricing and assess their relative importance.


## Research Question

How do property features and time on market influence rental prices in Toronto?

## Predictors examined include:

Number of bedrooms
Number of bathrooms
Rental unit size
Building type
Pet-friendliness
Days on market

The response variable is:

Rental price
Methodology
Data Preparation
Cleaned and transformed rental listing data
Converted dates into days-on-market measurements
Removed outliers using the Interquartile Range (IQR) method
Handled missing and non-standard values
Standardized variables for modelling
Statistical Modelling

Two candidate multiple linear regression models were developed and compared.

## Model diagnostics included:

Residual analysis
Q-Q plots
Multicollinearity assessment using Variance Inflation Factors (VIF)
ANOVA model comparison
AIC and BIC evaluation
Adjusted R² comparison
Box-Cox transformation assessment
Key Skills Demonstrated
Statistical Analysis
Multiple Linear Regression
Model Selection
Diagnostic Testing
Hypothesis Testing
Multicollinearity Analysis
Data Analysis
Data Cleaning
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Outlier Detection
Feature Engineering

